# Project 3
Cloud Infrastructure with Terraform

Core Objectives
- Create an entire environment
- Get end-to-end Terraform experience

TechStack
IaC Tool  - Terraform, HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language)
Cloud Provider  -  Azure (though Terraform is cloud-agnostic)
Automation  -  Azure DevOps to automate workflows & ArgoCD for GitOps deployments

Steps
- Write Terraform configuration scripts
- Define resources like VMs, storage
- Use modules for repeatable configs
- Use Terraform lifecycle (init, apply)
 
Time Investment
Very time taking for beginners

Potential Problems
Terraform can look scary at first, but it is highly in-demand tool worth your time
You may run into authentication/provider issues when connecting Terraform to your cloud account

